<font color="#FF0000">BEYOND VIET NAM</font><br>
<tt>Sun Dec  8  9:54:13 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I recently wrote a poem about the AIDS quilt that included<br>
images from the Viet Nam Memorial.  It occured to me <br>
afterwards that I am the only person I know in my current <br>
life who really remembers the war firsthand.  I was the <br>
daughter of an Air Force officer and the wife of an Army <br>
lieutenant at the time and went from believing in America's<br>
role to mistrusting all forms of government.  And for years<br>
I considered it a closed chapter in my own life as I watched<br>
vets struggle with the aftermath.  My current friends of my<br>
own age have no association with the war. <br>
I am becoming aware of how that period has affected my <br>
subsequent life and how there is a lot I have to work <br>
through.  <br>
Please maintain this site for some time to come.  It is my<br>
closest contact with others who realize what a turbulent<br>
tie that was.
<p><code>-- pnolan96@aol.com  (Pat Nolan) </code><p>


